column5:
2012 Masters thesis I would like to acknowledge my supervisors; Prof.
  Nancy M. Salem, Prof. Ahmed Farag Seddik and Prof. Mohamed Ibrahim El Adawy;
  for their great guidance and thorough review of my thesis

column11:
  For a prime $p\equiv 3$ $(\text{mod }4)$, let $h(-8p)$ and $h(8p)$ be the
class numbers of $\mathbb{Q}(\sqrt{-2p})$ and $\mathbb{Q}(\sqrt{2p})$,
respectively. Let $\Psi(\xi)$ be the Hirzebruch sum of a quadratic irrational
$\xi$. We show that $h(-8p)\equiv
h(8p)\Big(\Psi(2\sqrt{2p})/3-\Psi\big((1+\sqrt{2p})/2\big)/3\Big)$ $(\text{mod
}16)$. Also, we show that $h(-8p)\equiv 2h(8p)\Psi(2\sqrt{2p})/3$ $(\text{mod
}8)$ if $p\equiv 3$ $(\text{mod }8)$, and $h(-8p)\equiv
\big(2h(8p)\Psi(2\sqrt{2p})/3\big)+4$ $(\text{mod }8)$ if $p\equiv 7$
$(\text{mod }8)$.

